
[1]disaffection

   DISAFFECTION, n.

   1. Alienation of affection, attachment or good will; want of affection;
   or more generally, positive enmity, dislike or unfriendliness;
   disloyalty. It generally signifies more than indifference; as the
   disaffection of people to their prince or government; the disaffection
   of allies; disaffection to religion.

   2. Disorder; bad constitution; in a physical sense. [Little used.]
